caption: Had great convo with the owner, the food was amazing. Had a last minute bite to eat on our last day in town and couldn't have asked for a better experience. Definitely recommend.
Great po boys, fast service, and was taken care of great by the owner with some great personality! A must stop for everytime I'm in town!

Came here for a shrimp po boy and was not disappointed. The flavor was great! The restaurant has a lot of memorabilia hanging in the walls which was cool to look at. It took a little while to be served, may have come at an odd time, but the service was great. Felt like a place which would attract regulars.
Pleasant environment with good food.

A pleasant family-style restaurant experience in the French Quarter.  The staff is sensational and incredibly friendly!  The Po-boy sandwich is pretty good, but not earth-shattering.  It's an excellent place to grab a bite and wind-down after a long day of exploring the city.  Remember, it is a popular stop, so be ready to fight the crowd. With that said, it's still a must-try during your visit.
Clean, fast, family like friendly. Roast beef was to die for. Home cooking at its finest

Service was excellent. Definitely got that family owned feeling. Owner was extremely personable and the po-boy was huge! Felt good to support a local business that was right down the block from our hotel. Lots of history behind this place!

Mike was extremely personable and welcoming. If you manage to catch them when they're open it is worth the time to stop and have a bite to eat. The sports bar atmosphere was pretty cool and despite being from Michigan I was still made to feel right at home since Mike has a huge collection of sports memorabilia and cool stories from all over the country. A great, family owned restaurant is exactly the kind of place I was looking forward to eating at while visiting NOLA and Mike's place didn't disappoint. I will be sure to stop by again if I ever make it back down.
I really love the decor and the food tasted great I will be back and I will let other people know about this place
This place has a cool feel to it. They have a lot of positive reviews for a reason.

I wonder if these people have ever been introduced to salt and pepper. Their minds would be blown! This is what happens when you average the average of the averages of meh places in new Orleans. A terrible po boy, terribly overpriced (sadly, like most places in new Orleans eateries) bland as hell (again, a little salt and pepper would go a long way! Hint-hint). To be fair, Onion rings were yummy.
Service is consistently good. The place has a great atmosphere.
Food was good but all our food came out at different times.

Mike's Po-Boys is part of the classic New Orleans experience -- good food with an even better experience. The made-to-order sandwiches and hand battered onion rings pair perfectly to make an excellent lunch, all for less than $20. If you're ever near the French Quarter, head on over to Mike Serio's!
Good shrimp po boy and not bad sausage one. Buy one get one beer was nice. Great service.
GOATED
Delicious poboys!

Not only are the po boys very mediocre at best , the restaurant is filthy. I hope you will take the time to give it a good cleaning during this covid time. Also they don 't offer mayo, which I find odd.
Very clean welcoming place. Food was fresh and delicious. Very inexpensive quick stop
We ordered the Cuban and Roast Beef Po boy both were delicious and reasonably priced
Onions rings are amazing
A good place for a simple, yet tasty, quick served poboy with friendly staff and no frills.
Visiting from Arizona. Came in today and met Mike. Very nice gentleman. Had the roast beef po boy. It was awesome! We will be back.
Great po-boys!  Love the LSU stuff everywhere.
Awesome food and service.
Good Cuban sandwiches
I’m currently eating here right now and place is amazing! Food is great service is wonderful. Staff very helpful and patient. Will come back often
Great food , very friendly staff the muffaletta sandwich was delicious that's what they're famous I will definitely go back when I visit New Orleans again!
Awful just awful
Great little locals deli. Prices were good and so were the portions.
Great place!
Great place for a bite to eat! He beat Bobby Flay in a muffuletta throw down! The Hot Sicilian and Maddie Fries are great too!

The grilled shrimp po boy sandwich was so good! The staff was friendly and the service was quick. I ordered mine to go, but you can eat there. They also have cold bottled/canned beverages and bagged chips. It was a great place to try my first authentic po boy during my first visit to New Orleans.  I would definitely get lunch from here again.
The Roast Beef Po-Boy is a religious experience that is not to be missed
Good food.  Good prices. Get you some.
BIG AND YUMMY. Very hot in the restaurant tho.
Delicious
The owner served us himself and was super friendly and welcoming. The food was excellent! We had shrimp poboys, muffalata, fries. Onion rings in our group. Loved it! Great for first time visitors!
Goos local sandwich shop.  Got a Cuban and loved it,  the wife got a delicious roast beef poboy. Would recommend for a quick lunch.

I would like to give the owners of Serio's some love and thank them for opening their doors at 3:10pm (after closing) so that we could get a muffaletta before leaving town.  We had NO idea they closed at 3pm (didn't even check) and I was about in tears when the doors were locked.  Thank you so much for letting us in!  Can't come to New Orleans without getting a Serio's muffaletta (and the cuban our friends got was equally amazing)!!!

Ordered fried oyster po-boy to go. Pretty decent good. Place is a typical deli. Average wait time for food to be ready. Good pick up for a quick bite. I probably spend the time to sit down and dine here.
Awesome service and food. Thank you.

This place is dirty and smells awful. I should have trusted my first impression and walked right out again. But I was hungry and trusted other people's good ratings so I had a salad which made me feel queezy for hours.
Had the roast beef and the Italian, loved them both. Cheers🥂⚜️
Best Roast Beef Poboy I've had in years!
Inexpensive traditional new orleans po boys less than a block off canal street. Roast beef recommended. Dressed.
Serio's is the greatest and always a must, when I'm in nola.
Excellent Po-Boys.  If you want a true New Orleæns PO- Boy experience this is the place.  Good food, and good atmosphere.
Solid lunch spot
The Po-Boys are out of this world!
Muffeleta was good, Cuban po boy was excellent, Mike is super friendly
Must say this time the food was just ok I've eaten here before and the the food was way better guess different cooks

Best sandwich I've ever had. The quality of the meat was perfect in all of texture, taste and tempurature. There was hardly any wait time and while it was unavoidable to make a small mess, the wraping that it came in was large enough to cover my lap.
Great roast beef po-boy. Sloppy with great French bread. A New Orleans classic.
Amazing poboys. The Cuban was out of this world good.
Air Conditioner did not work in my room.  I would have never stayed here if I knew my room would be 80'F at night.
My first time I go back soon
Food was outstanding. Although my wife thought the bathroom was scarry
Great poboys, very friendly staff.
Awesome sandwich!!
Fresh bread and friendly service.
Good PO Boys, good price...

Worst meatball poboy me and my father have ever had.  3 tiny dry meatballs on a 10 inch stale piece of bread. Sauce was from the can also.  6 meatballs on 2 sandwhichws for 30 dollars total.  DO NOT EAT HERE
Seriously the best po boys! We visited 3 times in one weekend while visiting NOLA!
Tasty po boy
Better food and service in the city, but location is great
Very good comfort food.

Note this place closes at 3 pm. The food was good. But why I order a Poboy in New Orleans, I expect it to have a lot more meat on it than these had. You could choose to have your meat fried or grilled. I chose a grilled shrimp PoBoy. My husband a grilled catfish. The layer of shrimp on the sandwich did not cover all the bread. They did allow me to determine how much spice was in the shrimp. I need my mild. The catfish one needed twice as much meat to look decent. The next day while traveling home we stopped at a whole in the wall place near Birmingham AL. It had over twice as much fish on a square piece of bread than Serio's had on it's hoggiie roll.
Warm and tasty roast beef. Could be a little more meat for the price, esp compared to nearby establishments. Still great.
Great Po' boys!!   Way better than the dry po' boy we tried on Saturday.
Poboys are always awesome
Great Sandwich
Friendly service, good food, and fair prices.
best freakin' po-boy around!

This is one of those get you by places, something to get you over till you are ready for your actual meal. The people are nice but the food isn't very flavorful but like I said nice enough to get you through.
Food was ok small side on poboy
Great sandwiches everytime we visit New Orleans.  You'll leave with a yum on your face:)
Great shrimp poboys! Yum!
Great service, great food, great prices

Great mufalita! Nice deli with a variety of sandwich and po boy choices.  Common stop for locals that work downtown.  We decided to try this place in order to avoid the crowds at center grocery.  Glad we did.  Best mufalata I have had.
Great food, great hospitality, great atmosphere
Not terrible, it was a messy thing with not much meat. First night of Mardi gras but they were not as busy as you'd think.
Great poboys and people. A must visit
We ordered fried oyster po-boys. The oysters were delicious, but there were not enough of them. The bread was a little tough. It was just okay. And a little pricey.
Just plain old over priced sandwich. Hardly anything on it. Had the catfish po boy.
Huge sandwiches

The Po-boy is king here. And this is an institution, so you have to come. It must be good, because how could they be open 4 hours a day 6 days a week, and survive. Here's my feeling: there are way better po-boys around. I had the oyster-shrimp, and it was hot and fresh fried oyster with not quite so hot fresh shrimp. Dressed with mayo, shredded iceberg and a slice of tomato. The roll, was of the industrial production variety. So, good, not great. Not overflowing with fillings, as you might expect for the price. But I got to sit next to an impressive statue of Mike the Tigre. And I think I was served by the owner/proprietor. So lots of love. Check the box and try again elsewhere in my quest for a great po-boy
Excellent grits and shrimp.
Place is great.  Po-Boy was awesome. Service was nice, got my food fast 🙌👊👍
Great servicei!
Great food 😎😊👍

Good local place. Poboys were good. We got the shrimp, greenie, Saints and roast beef ones. Meats were tasty and full of flavor. The poboy doesn't keep shape after a few minutes of being soaked in the juices. With the Greenie, no juices, you could taste the quality of the bread. A bit dry and tough like other reviews. Overall, a good place for poboys.
The Muffeletta was very good, the staff is nice.
old school new orleans
The food was real good here
Awesome
This is a historic restaurant with great food
Best meal I ate in New Orleans.  Utterly perfect sandwiches.

We've been to New Orleans several times and have always wanted to stop in here, but never had the luck because they were always closed. They have very limited hours of 11am-3pm Monday - Saturday. However this time we made specific plans to get here as soon as they opened and were glad we did.  This place never looks busy, but don't let looks fool you because their service is great and they make some really good poboys. Definitely worth trying.
Great sandwich and fries.  Loved the friendly service.
(Translated by Google) Sensational  (Original) Sensacional
Very good sandwiches. Mickey is the best. Prices normal.
This is a great po-boy shop. Made to order and great bread. It’s an LSU fan must hit spot. Mike is a gem.
Great food and people
Good po boys
Awesome po-boy selection. Great staff. Great place to keep the good times rolling.
The staff is AMAZING.  The room was clean and very comfortable.  The location is in walking distance of most attractions.  I would stay there again.
Food was outstanding !
Bread is a little tough but overall great place and po-boys!
Love the sandwiches
The owner is extremely friendly and the food is delicious.
The Best!
Visited in my trip to Essence.  Good!
Good food and very friendly service
The fried shrimp po' boy sandwich and onion rings were delicious!
Great food
It was good food
Good fresh food!!!
VERY friendly service. Genuinely nice people and good food too!
Cool place, featured on 1 of the tv food shows...I got the Tiger, nice lil sandwich, but really (being from Jersey) it's just an Italian Cheeseburger, lol...go anyway, it's good!
Good and fast
Good poor boy and never seems to be too crowded.
Good, messy roast beef po-boy.
I really liked the Tiger Po Boy!
Great Po Boy even better price!
This is what I came to New Orleans for. Great food! I had a fried shrimp Po Boy and and the Maddie fries. Both were awesome;
The fried shrimp po boy was so good I almost cried
Delicious food. Simple and amazing.
Yummy roast beef po-boy.
Perfect for a casual lunch.we were in and out in 45 minutes.
This is a great sandwich shop with good food. It’s quick and fresh but do not expect fancy as again it’s a sandwich shop.
We came in from the rain while waiting for a Mardi Gras parade.  Had one of the best Bloody Mary's ever.  Great sandwich selection! And, they let us hang out until parade time,
Awesome roast beef po boy!
Good new Orleans style po boys.
The sandwiches are decent, but deserve better than the owner's casual anti-immigrant and anti-NFL-protester ramblings.
There are better P.O.-Boys to be found in the Big Easy.
The poboys were awesome, and staff was super kind.
Awesome food, a must stop for NOLA lunch.
Nothing special about this place. Actually the sandwiches we had were pretty bland. It's okay if you're in a rush, but if you're looking for a quality po' boy, I would look elsewhere.

The roast beef po boy is one of the best sandwiches I’ve ever eaten in my life. Anywhere. In the world. It is that good.  I hardly ever give five stars, but I can’t see giving anything less in this case. Even the fries were fresh and excellent.  I now consider this a not to be missed casual meal restaurant in New Orleans.
Great Food and Great Service. I'd recommend the Roast Beef Po-Boy.
Not too bad if you're in a hurry!
Sadly this was one of the worst shrimp Po boys I have ever eaten. Cannot recommend.
Decent po boys  but damn quick and good service. Family owned restaurant. Worth the visit.

I work in the CBD, and go here often for lunch. This place has great poboys, salads, and muffalettas. I particularly love the Maddie's Fries side item, it eats like a meal, and their Fried Fish Poboy is delicious. This place has the distinction of having had their cook beat Bobby Flay on a Muffalettas competition, and is decked out in LSU paraphernalia. It's not fancy, but the food is good and the service is quick.
Fresh, good tasting poboys at a reasonable price!
Not a friendly place. Turkey on my sandwich was completely dwarfed by the tasteless extra chewy bread. Can't believe they charge $8 for it. Extremely sad to say Subway is better.
Great sandwich

Took my husband here for birthday lunch!  It was SO yummy!  We split a "half" muffuletta (one of the better ones I have had), onion rings (perfect mix of crunch and tender), and potato salad (homemade and a MUST try!).  We were NOT disappointed and it was worth the walk from our hotel.  Mike is great to chat with as we all love a good football story!  The fact that he has a helmet from the ID Vandals (you still need a Boise State and Idaho State one) was a fun and we hope you make a trip Northwest to see our beautiful country!
Nawlins experience
Great sandwiches. Just off the beaten path enough it's easy to get to but not crazy crowded.
Great po-boys, friendly staff, highly recommend.

Me and my wife had the pleasure of dining in on Saturday morning 12/31/16 and it was absolutely delicious.. such a personal setting and friendly service. Especially enjoyed the conversation with the owners son and staff while eating and watching the LSU game. We will be back on our next visit to NO for sure.
Foods great, service is so-so
Great Po-Boys ask for more remoulad
Great poboys and service!
So many other better places you could go than here. Don't waste your time, money or calories. The shrimp po boy was gross. The cook didn't wash his hands after rubbing his snotty nose.

A must do for every visit to New Orleans.  Sandwiches were amazing.  Get the "half".  It's more than you can eat, but the other quarter will make a great late night snack.  The frozen hurricanes were some of our favorite drinks of our whole trip.
Wonderful service, we accidentally came in right before they closed and they still gave us a warm poboy. Tasted great. Thanks to the management!
Great food! This is a New Orleans landmark

We almost walked past, but a gentleman who was leaving told us the food was great. He was right.  The dining room is floor to ceiling LSU and Mike the Tiger themed, including a large tiger statue and tiger striped motorcycle. I ordered the "Tiger", a 2/3lb hamburger-poboy hybrid, and my wife had the Saint special. Both were large and delicious, and served quickly. The counter staff are friendly, and pleasantly chatty - you can tell they enjoy being there.
Been there twice this week.   Had the roast beef poboy-Wonderful!  Today I had the Mickey with Maddies frys- outstanding!
Not open Sunday as advertised
Po-boys are to small for the price

First time in New Orleans and I knew we had to try a muffalett. Mike's is a true treasure of the city. The establishment was clean and the staff was extremely friendly. So glad I won the "discussion" on where to eat!!!! My newly turned 18 yr old very picky eating daughter commented the Big papa was by far the best sandwich she has ever had. Love this place!!!!
Amazing hot sausage poboy.

I ate a 9th Ward Po Boy at 2 PM, by 8 PM I was slammed with an obvious food borne illness that included severe diarrhea, and violent vomiting obviously caused by my lunch which did not taste right at the time of consumption at this filthy establishment.  This place ruined my one evening I had planned in the French Quarter!  Do not eat here unless you want the chance of food poisoning!
Very busy when we went for the parade. Delicious.
Hands down, best bloody mary I've ever had!! Sandwiches were awesome, too!
So much less crowded than all the nearby places. Reasonable prices. There's a decent spread of sandwiches, and a very tasty bloody mary.

When you're ordering your food, take a look behind the counter. It is a dirty mess crawling with cochroaches. I live in the area and the food was subpar to any other nearby. Do yourself a favor and put this location on your blacklist.
One of the best Muffalettas in New Orleans... Great people and fair prices. I eat there at least once a week. The Roast Beef Po-boy is great too.
Had the roast beef poboy and onion rings, all very good. Will be returning.
A very well known local place to get a fantastic muffolatta
Too much bread. Not enough meat. Didn't accept credit cards. Look elsewhere.

The muffelaletta was good (but not great), and the turkey po'boy was one of the worst I ever had. It had so much Italian dressing that it was dripping with grease.  No vegetarian option for a sandwich. This was a real lunch disappointment.
The best muffs around. The "half" is bigger then you think!

what is so great about a po-boy? it is merely a sub sandwich with thick, chewy french bread that is difficult to bite....nothing really wrong with this place, lots of cool LSU memorabilia, but nothing really special
